headline: Netflix Stock Drops Again. Elon Musk Is Still Slamming the Streamer.
summary: Netflix  stock was down again on Thursday, amid a conservative backlash centered on the creator of an animated TV show.  Since Tuesday,  Tesla  CEO Elon Musk has been sharing and responding to X posts calling for people to boycott the streaming service.  “Same,” Musk wrote on X Tuesday, in response to a post where a user said they had canceled their Netflix subscription.

headline: Taylor Swift's 'The Life of a Showgirl' Arrives Oct. 3: Here's How to Shop Target's Exclusives and Midnight Releases
summary: Target Corporation (NYSE: TGT) announced that Taylor Swift's 12th studio album, "The Life of a Showgirl," will release Oct. 3 featuring exclusive items available only at Target. Guests can preorder now at Target.com or line up for the midnight release at select stores across the country.

headline: TRIP Achieves $100M in Profitable Revenue, Accelerating U.S. Expansion to Over 10,000 Doors with Whole Foods Exclusive Flavor Launch
summary: TRIP, the #1 Calming Beverage Globally, is accelerating its U.S. growth this fall with major retail wins and new flavor launches. Following best-in-category velocity in Target and Sprouts in H1 2025, TRIP is now available at Whole Foods Market, H-E-B, Spec's, Total Wine, United Supermarkets, Wegmans, Mother's, Giant and Haggen, cementing its position as a leader in the emerging calm category.

headline: Target Debuts Collection of New and Exclusive Products for Universal Pictures' 'Wicked: For Good'
summary: Target Corporation (NYSE: TGT) today announced an all-new collection inspired by Universal Pictures' "Wicked: For Good." The assortment features nearly 200 new products, with nearly half the assortment exclusive to Target and priced under $20. Fans can shop their favorites and find affordable gift options. The collection will begin rolling out Oct. 5 in Target stores and on Target.com with additional product drops leading up to the film's release only in theaters on Nov. 21.
